Title: Vibe Coding is a Dangerous Fantasy
Description: Last week, X exploded when a ‚Äúvibe coder‚Äù announced his SaaS was under attack. His business, built entirely with AI assistance and ‚Äúzero hand-written code,‚Äù was experiencing bypassed subscriptions, maxed-out API keys, and database corruption. His follow-up admission made this notable: ‚Äúas you know, I‚Äôm not technical so this is taking me longer than usual to figure out.‚Äù As someone deeply immersed in the AI code generation space, I‚Äôve been watching this unfold with a mix of sympathy and frustration. Let me be clear ‚Äî I‚Äôm not against AI-assisted development. My own tool aims to improve code generation quality. But there‚Äôs a growing and dangerous fantasy that technical knowledge is optional in the new AI-powered world. After observing many similar (though less public) security disasters, I‚Äôve come to a controversial conclusion: vibe coding isn‚Äôt just inefficient ‚Äî it‚Äôs potentially catastrophic.

Title: I used AI to write tests for my .NET application... Here's what happened
Description:
Want to master Clean Architecture? Go here: https://bit.ly/3PupkOJ
Want to unlock Modular Monoliths? Go here: https://bit.ly/3SXlzSt
Get the source code here: https://www.patreon.com/milanjovanovic

In this practical walkthrough, I explore how AI can transform the often tedious process of writing unit tests for .NET applications. Starting with a tour of my semi-complex .NET project, I explain its real-world use cases and demonstrate some existing test implementations. The video reveals why providing AI (specifically using Cursor) with example tests dramatically improves its ability to generate high-quality unit tests that match your coding standards and patterns. Watch as I demonstrate the complete workflow - from generating unit tests for the Domain layer to troubleshooting and fixing AI-generated code errors, and finally running the successful tests in Visual Studio.

We'll then extend the approach to the Application layer, showing how this technique can be applied across different parts of your architecture. Whether you're looking to reduce testing bottlenecks or improve your coverage, this step-by-step guide shows exactly how AI can become a valuable addition to your .NET development toolkit.
